# Environment variables for PreflopRange.
# Copy this file to ".env" (gitignored) and fill in real values for LOCAL dev.
# On Railway, set the same variables in the service's Variables tab instead.
# NEVER commit real secrets.

# Supabase Postgres connection string (Track D, D.1-api).
# Where: Supabase dashboard -> top-bar "Connect" button -> Direct tab ->
# "Session pooler" (there is NO "Database" item in Project Settings anymore).
# For an always-on app server (Railway / local) use the *Session pooler* string
# (IPv4-friendly), NOT the "Direct connection" (IPv6-only). Format:
#   postgresql://postgres.<project-ref>:<db-password>@aws-1-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
#   (the region prefix is aws-1 for this project; copy the live value, don't guess)
# Leave blank to run without a database: the app falls back to JSON files and
# /api/db/health reports {"configured": false}.
DATABASE_URL=

# Owner of all journaled answers until auth lands (Track D, D.1-api-write).
# A plain UUID, NOT a secret. Optional — journal.py defaults to
# 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001 if unset. Used only when auth is OFF
# (SUPABASE_URL unset); in DB+auth mode the real JWT subject replaces it.
DEV_USER_ID=

# ---- Auth (Track D, D.2) --------------------------------------------------
# Setting SUPABASE_URL turns auth ON: protected endpoints require a valid JWT,
# and the frontend shows the login gate. Leave BOTH blank to run single-user
# with no login (current prod behaviour). Set both together in prod.
#
# SUPABASE_URL — your project URL, e.g. https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
#   NOT a secret (the ref is visible in the dashboard URL). Used to fetch the
#   PUBLIC JWKS key for verifying token signatures (ES256) — no JWT secret is
#   ever stored. Where: Supabase dashboard -> Project Settings -> Data API/API.
SUPABASE_URL=
#
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY — the anon / publishable key. Public by design (shipped to
#   the browser to init supabase-js); served to the frontend via
#   /api/auth/config. This is NOT the service_role key — never put service_role
#   anywhere in code, env that reaches the client, or docs.
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
